  "curation": {
    "synopsis": "The Lost cycle closes on the fortress-world of Jago, where the Tanith First is rotated forward to a long-disused Imperial citadel called Hinzerhaus — a half-buried sandstone pile dug into a cliff face overlooking a chokepoint pass. Their orders are to anchor the Imperial left flank against an expected Arch-Enemy counter-attack. But Hinzerhaus itself is wrong: doors that open onto bare rock, sentries who vanish on watch, voices on the wind that whisper warnings the regiment is too dug-in to obey. The Ghosts settle into a siege-defence rhythm against waves of Blood Pact attackers while the citadel slowly reveals itself as a haunted place with its own designs. The novel deliberately reads as a horror-register war story — Hinzerhaus is closer to a haunted house than a fortification. Major regiment trauma lands by the end; the Tanith come out smaller and quieter, and The Lost cycle ends with the survivors marching off Jago as a permanently changed unit.",
